<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's a proud mother to three gorgeous children.</p>

<p>And on Wednesday, Elsa Pataky was seen treating her gorgeous twin boys to ice cream as she conducted the school run in Byron Bay, NSW.</p>

<p>The glamorous model, 44, looked effortlessly chic as she stepped out to greet her sons Tristan and Sasha, six, and take the pair back to the colossal mansion she shares with husband Chris Hemsworth, 37.</p>

<p>Treats! On Wednesday, Elsa Pataky (centre) was seen treating her two sons to ice cream as she conducted the school run in Byron Bay, NSW. Pictured: Elsa alongside her twin boys, Tristan and Sasha</p>

<p>For the occasion, Elsa wore an airy cream cotton blouse, which she teamed with a pair of loose-fitting trousers of the same material.</p>

<p>The doting mum, who went barefoot for the walk home, sported a stone fedora to shield herself from the sun.</p>

<p>She whisked her hair into a low ponytail, and appeared to wear no make-up for the occasion.</p>

<p>Effortlessly chic: For the occasion, Elsa wore an airy cream cotton blouse, which she teamed with a pair of loose-fitting trousers of the same material</p>

<p>Elsa appeared in high spirits as she ate her vanilla ice lolly and basked in the Spring sunlight.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, one of her sons sported dinosaur trousers and a police uniform shirt as he ate a Milo ice cream after a full day at school.  </p>

<p>Spanish starlet Elsa married Thor actor Chris in 2010, and the couple live in a $20million mega-mansion in Byron Bay with their twin boys and daughter India Rose, eight.</p>

<p>So sleek: The doting mum, who went barefoot for the walk home, sported a stone fedora to shield herself from the sun</p>

<p>In an interview with GQ Australia in 2018, Chris admitted that he struggled to understand how his sons can be 'so different' despite being twins.</p>

<p>'Tristan is so athletic but there's not an aggressive bone in his body,' he admitted.</p>

<p>'He's the most emotional one. Whereas Sasha is like a little gangster.'</p>

